Description: Fragment of a seal-impression. The fine brown Nile clay with some mica inclusions was hardened after excavation. The rear shows a bent surface with an impression like from a leather bag. In the break impressions of a turned cord with a width of 0.15 cm. The front side is covered with finger-impressions and bears an impression of an oval scarab-like seal. It shows a small Hr-face at the left (D2), to the right a wadjet eye (D10) with eyebrow.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
